 Educational Background



 


University of Virginia - McIntire School of Commerce

                  The McIntire School of Commerce is regarded as one of the nation's finest business schools, offering world-class programs at both the undergraduate and graduate level. McIntire’s undergraduate program offers students a Bachelor of Science in Commerce degree; students may choose to concentrate in Finance, Accounting, Marketing, Management, or Information Technology.                




 


University of Virginia - School of Law

                  Founded by Thomas Jefferson in 1819, the University of Virginia School of Law is a world-renowned training ground for distinguished lawyers and public servants. Consistently ranked among the top law schools in the nation, Virginia has educated generations of lawyers, instilling in them a commitment to leadership, integrity and community service.

Virginia is justly famous for its collegial environment that bonds students and faculty, and student satisfaction is consistently cited as among the highest in American law schools. At Virginia, law students share their experiences in a cooperative spirit, both in and out of the classroom, and build a network that lasts well beyond their three years here.

With more than 20,000 students and a faculty of more than 2,100, the University of Virginia has been ranked first or second among the nation's public universities since 1984. The University's diverse intellectual life is open to law students: Up to 12 credits from other departments may be counted toward the J.D. degree.                




MBA 


University of Virginia - Darden School of Business

                  The University of Virginia Darden School of Business is one of the world's leading business schools, offering MBA, Ph.D. and Executive Education programs.The Darden School improves the world by developing and inspiring responsible leaders and by advancing knowledge.The unique Darden experience combines the case study method, the highest-ranked faculty whose research advances global managerial practice and business education, and a tight-knit learning environment to develop principled and complete leaders.                





 Career History



Chairman & Chief Executive Officer

                                    2001 - Current                


Optical Cable Corp.


                  Optical Cable Corp. specializes in fiber optic and copper communication cabling and connectivity products and solutions. Its activities include design and manufacture of copper cable, fiber optic cables, copper connectivity such as field terminable plugs, and test fixture assemblies; fiber optic connectivity such as fiber optic connectors and tools, enclosures, and others. It also provide cable management, freestanding racks and cabinets, rack accessories, shelving, and wall-mount racks and cabinets. The company was founded in 1983 and is headquartered in Roanoke, VA.                




Chief Financial Officer & Senior Vice President

                                    2000 - 2001                


Homebytes.com, Inc.


                  Part of Minnesota Mutual Cos., Inc., Homebytes.com, Inc. is a company headquartered in Richmond, VA. The firm operates an Internet-based national residential real estate brokerage.                




