Executive Profile
Neil D. Wilkin Jr.Chairman, Chief Executive Officer and President, Optical Cable CorporationAgeTotal Calculated CompensationThis person is connected to 2 Board Members in 2 different organizations across 3 different industries.See Board Relationships53$425,389As of Fiscal Year 2016
Background

		Mr. Neil D. Wilkin, Jr. has been the Chairman and Chief Executive Officer of Optical Cable Corp. since September 26, 2003 and has been its President since April 11, 2002. Mr. Wilkin serves as the Chairman and Chief Executive Officer of SMP Data Communications Inc., a subsidiary of Optical Cable Corp. He served as the Acting President of Optical Cable Corp. since December 2001 and served as its Senior Vice President and Chief Financial Officer since September 2001. He ... served as Senior Vice President, Chief Financial Officer and Treasurer of homebytes.com, Incorporated. He joined Homebytes in January 2000. He also was Senior Vice President and Chief Financial Officer of Owners.com, Inc., a subsidiary of Homebytes. He practiced law for over 5 years concentrating on mergers and acquisitions, corporate finance and general corporate matters. Mr. Wilkin worked at two law firms, McGuireWoods LLP in Richmond, Virginia and Kirkland & Ellis in Washington, D.C. He has been a Director of Optical Cable Corp. since September 2001. He served as Director of Luna Innovations Incorporated since May 2012 until May 08, 2015. He practiced with Coopers & Lybrand (a predecessor to PricewaterhouseCoopers) before returning to graduate business school and law school. Mr. Wilkin holds an MBA from the University of Virginia's Darden Graduate Business School, his JD from the University of Virginia, School of Law and his BS in Commerce with Distinction from the University of Virginia, McIntire School of Commerce.Read Full Background




